script. We [test][wp:Software Testing] that we don't produce
multiple links to the same page. We also test that if we define
a [reference][wp:reference] ourselves, the script doesn't
generate one as well.

Can we do [foo][wp:Foo], [bar][wp:Bar] and [baz][wp:Baz] on the
same line? And why not one in [german][wp-de:Foo] as well?

We \[wp:test] that we can escape the reference.

A [link][link] without a prefix is left as-is. Assumed to have
its reference be defined manually.

A [wiktionary link][wt:link] is also provided. One in a [foreign
tongue][wt-sv:tungomål] as well.

